er and cook <b>20 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b> or until al dente. Transfer to a deep serving dish, add lemon juice, reserved herbs and peeled broad beans, mix gently and adjust seasoning if needed. Allow to rest for a few minutes to absorb the liquid and serve warm sprinkled with chopped pistachio nuts."}],"hintsAndTricks":["The beans come out of their skin easily if you break the skin and press them gently between forefinger and thumb.","For a complete meal accompany this dish with meat or fish.","Freekeh (also called farik) is wheat harvested while young and green and undergoes a roasting process. It can be replaced with other whole grains like quinoa, brown rice, spelt or bulgur, in this case adjust cooking time accordingly."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","8 portions"]}